Recently, Ballantine and Welch [7] generalized and refined these two functions in numerous ways. One of the outcomes of their work was to consider PEND partitions and POND partitions, wherein the even (respectively, odd) parts are not allowed to be distinct. In a vein similar to that shared above, we let \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
